  "text": "In principle, similar analyses can be performed on time resolved photoluminescence (TRPL) transients. In 20 a surface recombination velocity of 2 × 10 4 cm/s was derived from TRPL transients of similar kesterite samples based on the analytic approximation (5) of the continuity equation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . However, the time resolution of a TRPL detector can lead to an underestimation of the initial decay and the TRPL maximum can occur significantly after carrier excitation, as shown in Fig. 5a , by convoluting the TRTS transient with typical TRPL response of ca. 300 ps full width half maximum. Both effects oppose a reliable mobility analysis and show the benefits of superior time resolution of TRTS.",
